00:13:35,600 --> 00:13:39,920
You want me to just sit and watch while they threaten my husband?
你要我就这样看着他们威胁我的丈夫吗？

181
00:13:41,400 --> 00:13:43,400
The real question is...
问题是

182
00:13:44,000 --> 00:13:48,120
Where did you find that stone, Selim?
塞利姆，你在哪里找到那块石头？

183
00:13:51,200 --> 00:13:54,400
It was really dark. Did you have to look long for it?
天很黑  你找了很久吗?

184
00:13:55,600 --> 00:14:00,640
Or did you scramble to find it, to get a stone in yourself?
还是你自己抢来的？

185
00:14:02,000 --> 00:14:03,040
Was that how it went?
那是怎么回事？

186
00:14:04,400 --> 00:14:06,360
If you really did that,
如果你真的做了

187
00:14:08,600 --> 00:14:11,680
then you're more dangerous than they are, Selim.
那你比他们更危险

188
00:14:13,520 --> 00:14:14,520
Step aside.
靠边

189
00:14:19,840 --> 00:14:21,600
Still no visitors.
仍然没有人拜访我

190
00:14:23,080 --> 00:14:24,880
They must've forgotten about me.
他们一定忘了我

191
00:14:26,040 --> 00:14:27,480
Don't be silly.
别傻了

192
00:14:28,040 --> 00:14:30,680
Your daughter calls every day. She'd never forget about you.
你的女儿每天都在打电话  她永远不会忘记你

193
00:14:31,640 --> 00:14:33,160
The shuttle was launched.
航天飞机发射了

194
00:14:35,040 --> 00:14:37,960
The shuttle was launched but still no visitors.
航天飞机发射了，但仍然没有人来找我

195
00:14:38,760 --> 00:14:41,120
They must've forgotten me here.
他们一定是忘了我

196
00:14:43,160 --> 00:14:44,720
The shuttle was launched.
航天飞机发射了

197
00:14:55,560 --> 00:14:56,640
Come on.
来吧

198
00:14:59,880 --> 00:15:02,840
- Weren't you scared? - Just watch.
-你不怕吗？-看着

199
00:15:04,040 --> 00:15:05,880
See the bloodstain?
看到血迹了吗？

200
00:15:08,560 --> 00:15:10,840
The aquarium was busted, as well.
鱼缸也被打碎了

201
00:15:12,160 --> 00:15:14,760
Suveyda. Come here.
苏薇达  过来

202
00:15:15,560 --> 00:15:17,320
Isn't that Mehmet Yurtgil?
那不是穆罕默德·尤尔吉尔吗？

203
00:15:19,000 --> 00:15:20,000
Point it at me.
指着我

204
00:15:23,640 --> 00:15:24,800
That's it.
就这样

205
00:15:27,160 --> 00:15:28,320
What did you do next?
接下来你做什么？

206
00:15:29,720 --> 00:15:30,720
What do you think?
你觉得怎么样？

207
00:15:32,320 --> 00:15:33,480
No way.
不可能吧

208
00:15:34,160 --> 00:15:35,200
Right then and there?
就在那里？

209
00:15:35,760 --> 00:15:38,960
Don't get too excited. We didn't record it.
别太兴奋  我们没有录制

210
00:15:39,040 --> 00:15:40,040
Shit.
该死

211
00:15:43,760 --> 00:15:46,720
Here you go. You can watch the rest of it later.
给你，你可以稍后看其他内容

212
00:15:49,160 --> 00:15:52,360
You won't find the footage in there anywhere else.
在其他任何地方都找不到素材

213
00:15:52,920 --> 00:15:55,040
We went to all the crime scenes.
我们去了所有犯罪现场

214
00:15:55,600 --> 00:15:57,520
So? Did you find any clues?
那你找到任何线索了吗？

215
00:15:58,120 --> 00:16:00,440
About who the guy might be, I mean.
我是说  凶手可能是谁

216
00:16:00,520 --> 00:16:03,520
- That's not the point. - What is it, then?
-那不是重点  -那什么是重点？

217
00:16:03,600 --> 00:16:05,080
Suveyda, show him.
苏薇达  给他看看

218
00:16:12,360 --> 00:16:14,120
Nevra's cat.
内芙拉的猫

219
00:16:15,120 --> 00:16:16,480
Cat cat psychopath.
猫猫精神变态

220
00:16:18,800 --> 00:16:19,680
What is this?
这是什么？

221
00:16:19,760 --> 00:16:23,760
Welcome to the fan club of Turkey's first legit serial killer.
欢迎来到土耳其首个合法的连环杀手粉丝俱乐部

222
00:16:23,840 --> 00:16:28,120
We had to find a nickname for the guy. Like Jack the Ripper.
我们要先给杀手起个绰号，就像开膛手杰克

223
00:16:28,200 --> 00:16:32,240
We wanted to find a nickname related to the stickers.
我们想找到一个与贴纸有关的绰号

224
00:16:32,880 --> 00:16:36,400
- We decided to start calling him Stick. - Stick.
-我们最开始决定称他为贴纸男  -贴指男

225
00:16:37,040 --> 00:16:38,080
That's good.
好啊

226
00:16:38,680 --> 00:16:43,000
We wanted to call him Writer at first, but we decided it would be silly.
本来想称他为作家，但我们觉得很蠢

227
00:16:43,680 --> 00:16:45,800
Then I thought about the cat costume.
然后我想到了猫服装

228
00:16:45,880 --> 00:16:47,560
This is what we came up with.
这就是最终我们想出来的

229
00:16:50,040 --> 00:16:51,880
- What are you doing? - Hold on.
-你在做什么？-别急

230
00:16:52,600 --> 00:16:53,760
DOG SLAYER
狗杀手

231
00:16:53,840 --> 00:16:56,680
- Here it is! - Holy fuck!
-就是它了  -卧槽！

232
00:16:56,760 --> 00:16:58,720
That's a great name!
真是个好名字！

233
00:16:59,360 --> 00:17:05,440
Suveyda didn't like it at all first. Killing dogs doesn't appeal to her.
苏薇达一开始就不喜欢  因为杀狗对她没有吸引力

234
00:17:05,520 --> 00:17:08,840
But I explained to her that it had nothing to do with dogs.
但我向她解释说，这与狗无关

235
00:17:08,920 --> 00:17:11,560
We all love dogs, right?
我们都爱狗，对吗？

236
00:17:12,120 --> 00:17:14,840
But that's not the point. This is something else.
但不是重点  这是另外一回事

237
00:17:17,200 --> 00:17:19,600
He's a cat. A cat that kills dogs.
他是猫  杀死狗的猫

238
00:17:20,520 --> 00:17:22,920
The weak triumphing over the strong.
弱者胜过强者

239
00:17:23,440 --> 00:17:27,000
It goes against everything we know. It goes against nature.
它违反了我们所知道的一切  违背了自然法则

240
00:17:28,160 --> 00:17:29,840
I think that's awesome.
我觉得很棒

241
00:17:31,400 --> 00:17:34,040
- I see. - We're almost there.
-我知道了-我们就快准备好了

242
00:17:34,120 --> 00:17:37,040
Just some finishing touches on the website and we go live.
网站还有一些收尾的工作，然后我们就嫩上线了

243
00:17:37,120 --> 00:17:38,200
What's missing?
还缺什么？

244
00:17:38,920 --> 00:17:41,880
A forum asking a question: Whom would you like Dog Slayer to kill?
一个论坛的问题：你希望狗杀手杀死谁?

245
00:17:41,960 --> 00:17:44,800
People will share on the forum whom they wish death on,
人们会在论坛上分享他们希望死亡的对象

246
00:17:44,880 --> 00:17:47,440
and why they deserve to die.
以及为什么他们应该死

247
00:17:48,000 --> 00:17:50,640
They will even vote on each other's victims.
他们甚至会投票给对方的受害者

248
00:17:51,560 --> 00:17:53,000
A list will emerge.
一个死亡清单即将出现

249
00:17:53,080 --> 00:17:56,080
Like a stock exchange but for prospective murder victims.
像证券交易所一样，但针对潜在的谋杀受害者

250
00:17:56,160 --> 00:17:57,520
That's rad.
太棒了

251
00:17:57,600 --> 00:18:01,880
Imagine Dog Slayer actually killing someone from that list.
想象一下杀是杀手真的杀死了名单上的某个人

252
00:18:03,040 --> 00:18:04,400
Why not?
为什么不呢？

253
00:18:14,080 --> 00:18:17,320
- Hold on. I'm almost done. - Sure.
-等一下  我快完成了  -当然

254
00:18:18,920 --> 00:18:22,160
- Take the chair over there. - I'm fine standing.
-坐那边的椅子  -我站着就行

255
00:18:25,480 --> 00:18:28,160
Have you ever heard about the village of Durucay?
你听说过杜鲁凯村吗？

256
00:18:29,760 --> 00:18:32,640
I worked at the courthouse there for a while.
我在那儿的法院工作过一段时间

257
00:18:32,720 --> 00:18:37,720
One day, our superiors told us we had to go to a mandatory seminar.
有一天，上司告诉我们，我们必须去参加强制性研讨会

258
00:18:37,800 --> 00:18:42,960
Some Americans came and made a deal with the ministry.
一些美国人前来与该部达成协议

259
00:18:43,600 --> 00:18:45,560
They were the ones holding the seminar.
他们是举行研讨会的人

260
00:18:46,720 --> 00:18:47,720
Anyway...
总之……

261
00:18:48,560 --> 00:18:52,280
I was working as a court clerk then. It's the most important job there.
那时候我是法院书记员，这是最重要的工作

262
00:18:52,920 --> 00:18:55,920
You have to write each and every word down,
你必须写下每一句话，

263
00:18:56,000 --> 00:18:57,680
never missing a single one.
永远不会漏掉任何一句

264
00:18:58,160 --> 00:19:02,720
- I'll wash up and be right back. - What? Sure, sure.
-我会洗干净然后马上回来  -什么？好的

265
00:19:09,240 --> 00:19:11,480
So we went to the seminar.
我们去了研讨会

266
00:19:12,760 --> 00:19:14,480
They gave us these...
他们给我们发了这种……

267
00:19:15,520 --> 00:19:16,720
These masks.
口罩

268
00:19:17,240 --> 00:19:20,520
Stenomasks, they were called.
他们被称之为速记口罩

269
00:19:20,600 --> 00:19:24,200
You speak into it. It's so sound-proofed that no one can hear what you're saying.
人们对着它说话非常的隔音，没人听见你在说什么

270
00:19:24,760 --> 00:19:29,680
It's connected to a recorder that records everything you say.
它连接着一个录音机，录下你所说的一切

271
00:19:29,760 --> 00:19:30,920
Anyway...
总之……

272
00:19:31,680 --> 00:19:34,280
So they gave me one and I started using it.
他们给了我一个，我开始使用它

273
00:19:34,360 --> 00:19:40,040
It was such a weird feeling, speaking and not having anyone hear you.
感觉很奇怪，说话时没有人听到你的声音

274
00:19:40,120 --> 00:19:44,000
It was so impressive that I started seeing it in my dreams.
令人印象深刻，我开始在梦中看到它

275
00:19:45,680 --> 00:19:46,680
For instance...
比方说

276
00:19:47,400 --> 00:19:50,120
I'm in a crowded place in the dream.
我在梦中拥挤的地方

277
00:19:50,200 --> 00:19:53,040
I speak and speak but no one can hear.
我会说话  但没人能听到

278
00:19:55,120 --> 00:19:57,400
You know what happened a few days ago?
你知道几天前发生了什么吗？

279
00:19:57,480 --> 00:20:01,920
I was waiting in line at the bank when a woman came to warn me.
我在银行排队等候时，一位女职员过来提醒我

280
00:20:02,000 --> 00:20:04,480
She told me I was speaking to myself.
她说我是在自言自语

281
00:20:04,560 --> 00:20:09,080
I was pretty shook up. Who knows what I'd told her.
我吓坏了  谁知道我跟她说了什么

282
00:20:09,160 --> 00:20:11,720
- Would you like some tea? - No, thank you.
-要喝茶吗  -不，谢谢

283
00:20:12,360 --> 00:20:13,840
It's funny how things change.
事情的变化很有趣

284
00:20:14,520 --> 00:20:20,440
I used to be terrified that no one would hear what I said.
我曾经很害怕没有人会听到我说的话

285
00:20:20,520 --> 00:20:22,560
Now, I'm terrified that they might.
现在，我很害怕他们可能会听到

286
00:20:23,840 --> 00:20:25,080
I guess...
我猜……

287
00:20:26,560 --> 00:20:27,560
That's life.
那就是人生

288
00:20:28,960 --> 00:20:30,520
What's wrong with your car?
你的车怎么了？

289
00:20:31,320 --> 00:20:32,960
My car's fine.
我的车很好

290
00:20:33,960 --> 00:20:35,520
I'm the one with the problem.
我就是那个有问题的人

291
00:20:45,320 --> 00:20:47,000
What have I done?
我做了什么？

292
00:20:48,480 --> 00:20:51,520
I forgot to ask him where Ufuk lived.
我忘了问他乌福克住的地方

293
00:20:52,480 --> 00:20:54,240
How am I supposed to find him now?
我现在应该怎么找到他？

294
00:21:10,680 --> 00:21:11,680
Hello?
喂？

295
00:21:12,280 --> 00:21:13,800
Hello? How do you answer this?
喂？这鬼东西怎么接啊？

296
00:21:14,400 --> 00:21:15,400
Hello?
喂？

297
00:21:15,760 --> 00:21:18,360
Hello? Ufuk?
喂？

298
00:21:19,360 --> 00:21:21,200
How do you answer this?
怎么接啊？

299
00:21:21,280 --> 00:21:23,200
Hello? Ufuk?
喂？乌福克？

300
00:21:33,840 --> 00:21:35,960
You were so good at this stuff, Mebrure.
你曾经很擅长用这些东西，梅布鲁雷

301
00:21:36,760 --> 00:21:40,320
You were so good at answering the phone and talking to the caller.
你很擅长接电话并和打电话的人交谈

302
00:21:40,960 --> 00:21:45,600
I asked you to teach me how but you kept putting it off. Now look at me!
我让你教我怎么做，但是你一直拖着，现在你看我！

303
00:21:45,680 --> 00:21:48,760
You went and left me, and here I am, all alone!
你走了，留下我一个人在这里!

304
00:21:49,520 --> 00:21:52,720
What am I supposed to do now? Whom am I supposed to ask for help?
我现在该怎么办？我该找谁帮忙？

305
00:21:53,560 --> 00:21:56,200
Am I supposed to ask them how to answer a phone?
我应该问他们如何接电话吗？

306
00:21:56,280 --> 00:21:57,880
Won't they mock me?
他们不会嘲笑我吗？

307
00:21:57,960 --> 00:22:00,400
An adult man who can't even answer a phone!
一个成年男人竟然不会接电话！

308
00:22:01,360 --> 00:22:05,840
See what you did? I'm over here talking to myself!
看看你对我做了什么？我在这里自言自语！

309
00:22:05,920 --> 00:22:08,360
He can't do anything! He can't even answer a phone!
他什么也做不了，甚至连电话都不会接！

310
00:22:08,440 --> 00:22:10,360
I wouldn't be talking to myself if you were here.
如果你在这里我就不会自言自语了

311
00:22:10,440 --> 00:22:14,680
That's what the woman at the bank said. I was talking to myself.
那是银行的女职员说的。我在自言自语

312
00:22:14,760 --> 00:22:16,720
Yes, but no one will hear what I'm saying.
是的，但是没人会听到我在说什么

313
00:22:16,800 --> 00:22:18,080
You don't hear what I'm saying.
你听不到我在说什么

314
00:22:18,160 --> 00:22:19,280
You don't hear!
你听不到

315
00:22:19,360 --> 00:22:22,480
No one listens! No one listens to me!
没有人听！没有人听我说！

316
00:22:33,720 --> 00:22:35,360
No one!
没人！

317
00:23:01,760 --> 00:23:03,840
- Good morning. - Good morning.
- 早上好  -早上好

318
00:23:04,440 --> 00:23:07,320
- Have you been waiting long? - No. I just got here.
-等了很久吗 -没有，我刚到

319
00:23:08,960 --> 00:23:10,800
Take me to the house.
带我去那房子

320
00:23:12,720 --> 00:23:14,640
UFUK EXPECTING YOU FOR DINNER IN KAMBURA
乌福克：在坎布拉等你吃饭

321
00:23:46,400 --> 00:23:48,080
You do hear me.
你听到了

322
00:23:48,160 --> 00:23:51,760
You should've wished for something bigger.
你应该期望更大的目标

323
00:23:53,120 --> 00:23:55,560
Just this morning, you said you wanted to see Kambura again,
就在今天早上，你说你想再看看坎布拉

324
00:23:55,640 --> 00:23:57,400
and here we are, on our way there.
现在我们就在过去的路上

325
00:23:57,480 --> 00:23:59,480
You're right.
是的

326
00:24:00,080 --> 00:24:05,400
When you asked me to cancel all your meetings, I was concerned.
当你要求我取消所有会议时，我很担心

327
00:24:05,480 --> 00:24:08,960
- Everything's alright, right? - Of course. Everything's alright.
-没事吧  -当然没事

328
00:24:09,760 --> 00:24:11,680
I want to see an old friend.
我想见一个老朋友

329
00:24:12,840 --> 00:24:16,200
We should have some fish. Our fish is unlike anywhere else's.
我们应该吃点鱼  那里的鱼与众不同

330
00:24:17,080 --> 00:24:18,520
And some raki, as well.
再来些葡萄酒

331
00:24:19,320 --> 00:24:20,680
You do drink, right?
你喝酒吧？

332
00:24:21,640 --> 00:24:24,080
It doesn't really agree with me.
它真的不适合我

333
00:24:24,760 --> 00:24:26,760
One glass of raki never hurt anyone.
一杯葡萄酒不会怎样的

334
00:24:29,600 --> 00:24:32,000
I've seen much more implausible reports before.
我之前看过很多令人难以置信的报道

335
00:24:32,080 --> 00:24:36,000
Reports declaring that a man shot from behind had killed himself.
报道称一名男子从背后开枪自杀

336
00:24:38,040 --> 00:24:41,280
- Welcome to Kambura. - It's a nice place.
-欢迎来到坎布拉  -这是一个好地方

337
00:24:41,360 --> 00:24:44,000
Like a fairy tale. Why don't you like it?
就像童话一样，你为什么不喜欢呢？

338
00:24:45,720 --> 00:24:49,720
Here are the red riding hoods, and there are the wolves.
这里有小红帽和大灰狼

339
00:24:49,800 --> 00:24:53,360
And mandatory happy endings no matter what comes to pass.
无论怎样都会有强制性的幸福结局

340
00:24:54,080 --> 00:24:58,000
It's a fairy tale, alright. We just need to find the narrator.
这是童话，好吧，我们只需要找到一个讲故事的人

341
00:24:58,880 --> 00:25:01,240
Selim or whomever it was that wrote that report.
塞利姆或撰写报告的人

342
00:25:09,560 --> 00:25:10,640
Ufuk!
乌福克！

343
00:25:11,440 --> 00:25:13,280
Ufuk, come and help me!
乌福克，过来帮帮我！

344
00:25:14,800 --> 00:25:16,800
Ufuk, I'm talking to you!
乌福克，我在叫你！

345
00:25:19,040 --> 00:25:22,800
- Let me finish my smoke. - Put it out!
-让我抽完烟  -把烟掐了！

346
00:25:24,440 --> 00:25:26,880
Have you lost your mind! What are you doing!
你疯了吗！你在做什么！

347
00:25:27,680 --> 00:25:29,680
What's one more scar?
还有什么伤疤?

348
00:25:32,240 --> 00:25:36,480
Ufuk! Ufuk! Where are you going, son?
乌福克！乌福克！儿子，你要去哪里？

349
00:25:37,880 --> 00:25:41,120
Has it been like this for ten years?  Why don't they tear it down?
十年来一直这样吗？为什么不把它拆了？

350
00:25:41,720 --> 00:25:44,920
I think they're so used to seeing it that they don't even notice it anymore.
我想他们已经习惯了，甚至都没有注意到它

351
00:25:45,000 --> 00:25:46,920
You can't tear down something you don't notice.
你不能拆毁你根本没有注意到的东西

352
00:25:47,520 --> 00:25:50,800
The people lost in the fire...
人们在大火中迷失了自我

353
00:25:51,400 --> 00:25:55,760
Tayyar Kaymak, 49. His wife, Songul Kaymak, 41.
49岁的塔亚尔·凯马克和他41岁的妻子松古尔·凯马克

354
00:25:55,840 --> 00:25:57,120
And their five children.
还有他们的五个孩子

355
00:25:57,760 --> 00:26:00,440
Seven people, all living in this tiny house?
七个人都住在这间小房子里？

356
00:26:00,960 --> 00:26:02,400
I read something in a novel once.
我曾经读过一部小说

357
00:26:02,480 --> 00:26:06,320
"Man takes less and less space the poorer he gets," it said.
书上说：“人越穷，占用的空间就越少。”

358
00:26:07,000 --> 00:26:10,520
The poorer you are, the smaller you can make yourself.
越穷，就越小

359
00:26:17,880 --> 00:26:22,040
So that's why the richer people get, the more space they need.
这就是为什么富人需要更多的空间

360
00:26:22,120 --> 00:26:24,280
Explains the gigantic houses.
解释了他们问什么有巨大的别墅

361
00:26:24,920 --> 00:26:26,960
How old was the youngest child?
最小的孩子几岁？

362
00:26:28,520 --> 00:26:29,560
Four months old.
四个月大

363
00:26:30,440 --> 00:26:31,640
Four months old.
四个月大

364
00:26:32,440 --> 00:26:34,080
In such a tiny house.
在这么小的房子里

365
00:26:34,840 --> 00:26:38,520
Could you go to sleep when you have a four-month-old here?
当你有一个四个月大的孩子时，你能睡着觉吗?

366
00:26:39,520 --> 00:26:42,680
I don't remember what I did as a four-month-old.
我不记得我四个月大时做了什么

367
00:26:45,920 --> 00:26:49,640
I'll tell you what you did. You cried nonstop.
你会不停地哭

368
00:26:51,200 --> 00:26:53,240
So how come the report says
那报告怎么这样写

369
00:26:53,320 --> 00:26:56,880
that they were presumed to have slept through the fire?
他们被推测在火灾中睡着了?

370
00:26:58,440 --> 00:26:59,480
All of them.
全都睡着了

371
00:26:59,560 --> 00:27:02,560
How's that possible? All seven of them, asleep.
那怎么可能呢？七个人都睡着了

372
00:27:02,640 --> 00:27:03,800
I already told you.
我已经跟你说过

373
00:27:04,400 --> 00:27:06,240
Whatever's in the report goes.
报告就是这样写的

374
00:27:07,120 --> 00:27:10,360
Tayyar Kaymak had some priors, right?
塔亚尔·凯马克有一些前科，对吧？

375
00:27:10,440 --> 00:27:13,480
Yes. Jailed twice, both times for burglary.
是的  两次入狱，两次都是入室盗窃

376
00:27:14,880 --> 00:27:15,960
Burglary...
入室盗窃

377
00:27:17,400 --> 00:27:18,920
If you were a thief...
如果你是小偷

378
00:27:19,000 --> 00:27:21,280
would you be living in this place with six other people
你会和另外六个人住在这个地方吗

379
00:27:21,360 --> 00:27:22,880
while also working the fields?
还在地里干活?

380
00:27:24,040 --> 00:27:25,280
Never.
决不

381
00:27:25,880 --> 00:27:31,720
I might start working the fields if I'd repented for my sins, though.
不过，如果我为自己的罪过忏悔，我可能会在田里干活。

382
00:27:32,560 --> 00:27:34,120
Tayyar wasn't a thief.
塔亚尔不是小偷

383
00:27:41,480 --> 00:27:44,160
Not a single one of the people who died in this house was a thief.
在这个房子里死去的人中没有一个是小偷

384
00:27:52,000 --> 00:27:54,640
- So... - Ufuk.
-所以……-乌福克

385
00:27:55,480 --> 00:27:56,480
Alright, Ufuk.
好的，乌福克

386
00:27:57,160 --> 00:27:58,360
Where were you burnt?
你在哪里被烧伤的？

387
00:27:59,480 --> 00:28:00,720
I was burnt here, as well.
我也时在这里被烧伤的

388
00:28:01,360 --> 00:28:03,640
I was trying to save them.
我想救他们

389
00:28:04,600 --> 00:28:05,760
Who started the fire?
谁扔的火把？

390
00:28:08,440 --> 00:28:09,520
I did.
我扔的

391
00:28:22,280 --> 00:28:24,040
I was standing right there.
我当时正站在那儿

392
00:28:24,120 --> 00:28:27,000
Everything flared up in an instant. I was startled.
一切突然爆发了  我被吓了一跳

393
00:28:28,000 --> 00:28:31,720
I thought they'd get out of the house after seeing the flames.
我以为他们看到火焰后会离开屋子

394
00:28:32,320 --> 00:28:35,760
But no one get out. The fire was getting bigger.
但没人出门  火势越来越大

395
00:28:36,400 --> 00:28:39,440
I could hear the screaming children inside.
我能听到里面的孩子在尖叫

396
00:28:39,520 --> 00:28:41,400
I could hear the children's screams!
我能听到孩子们的尖叫声！

397
00:28:42,440 --> 00:28:47,800
I ran to the door, but the door was chained and locked.
我跑到门口，但门被锁住了

398
00:28:47,880 --> 00:28:50,000
tried to break the chains, but I couldn't.
我试图打破锁链，但我做不到

399
00:28:50,600 --> 00:28:54,680
I ran to the other window. It was shut, as well.
我跑到另一个窗口，但也被封锁了

400
00:28:55,320 --> 00:28:56,320
I thought maybe...
我想也许

401
00:28:59,040 --> 00:29:00,600
I couldn't get anyone out!
我无法把任何人救出来！

402
00:29:03,000 --> 00:29:05,960
I shouted to the crowd! Help me, I said!
我向人群大喊！帮帮我！

403
00:29:06,040 --> 00:29:08,920
Let's break the chains together! Somebody help me!
我们把锁链打开！来人帮帮我！

404
00:29:09,000 --> 00:29:11,680
Nobody helped! Nobody broke the chains!
没有人帮助！没有人打开铁链！

405
00:29:11,760 --> 00:29:14,200
Nobody came! Nobody helped me!
没人来！没人帮助我！

406
00:29:14,760 --> 00:29:15,840
- Then... - Ufuk!
-然后……  -乌福克

407
00:29:16,720 --> 00:29:17,720
Ufuk!
乌福克！

408
00:29:20,520 --> 00:29:22,320
- Ufuk. - What?
-乌福克  -什么

409
00:29:23,960 --> 00:29:25,560
Who chained the doors?
谁把门锁住了？

410
00:29:26,560 --> 00:29:32,160
I asked them who did. They told me there were no chains.
我问他们是谁锁的  但他们告诉我没有锁链

411
00:29:32,840 --> 00:29:34,120
I was supposedly...
我应该是

412
00:29:35,120 --> 00:29:38,040
I was burnt while trying to rescue the family.
我在营救他们时被烧伤了

413
00:29:38,120 --> 00:29:39,880
A falling beam hit me on the head.
落下的横梁击中了我的头

414
00:29:39,960 --> 00:29:42,440
Ufuk, here's what we're going to do.
乌福克，我们接下来这样做

415
00:29:43,080 --> 00:29:45,160
- Ufuk, we're going... - Arrest me!
-Ufuk，我们要……  -逮捕我！

416
00:29:45,240 --> 00:29:46,880
- Sure, alright. - Arrest me!
-当然可以  -逮捕我！

417
00:29:46,960 --> 00:29:48,720
- Come with me. - Arrest me!
-跟我来  -逮捕我！

418
00:29:48,800 --> 00:29:51,200
- Sure. Fine. - I killed those children. Arrest me!
-好的  -是我杀了那些孩子  快逮捕我！

419
00:29:51,280 --> 00:29:52,160
- Sure. - Please!
-好的  -请！

420
00:29:52,240 --> 00:29:54,800
- Let's talk for a bit. - My face was burnt here!
-让我们谈谈-我的脸就是在这里被烧伤了！

421
00:29:54,880 --> 00:29:57,360
- Sure, come with me. - Arrest me, please arrest me!
-当然，跟我来  -逮捕我，请逮捕我！

422
00:29:57,440 --> 00:29:59,440
- Sure, I will. - Arrest me! See my scars?
-当然，我会的  -逮捕我！看到我的伤疤了吗？

423
00:29:59,520 --> 00:30:00,880
- Sure. - I burnt the house down!
-当然  -是我把房子烧毁了！

424
00:30:00,960 --> 00:30:03,280
- I understand. - I killed those children.
-我知道  -我杀了那些孩子

425
00:30:03,360 --> 00:30:06,160
- Alright, alright. - Please arrest me.
-好的  -请逮捕我

426
00:30:06,240 --> 00:30:09,480
Look at that house!  I'm the one who burnt it down!
看那所房子！我是烧毁它的人！

427
00:30:09,560 --> 00:30:13,160
- I understand. - The children! I burnt it all down!
-我明白了  -还有孩子们！我把它全部烧掉了！

428
00:30:31,680 --> 00:30:34,720
- The boy's talking. - Leave him be.
-他说了  -别管他了

429
00:30:35,640 --> 00:30:36,720
Let him talk.
让他说吧

430
00:30:45,400 --> 00:30:48,920
- You still haven't gotten married? - No.
-你还没结婚吗  -没有

431
00:30:50,160 --> 00:30:51,240
Of course.
当然

432
00:30:52,160 --> 00:30:55,760
You already have a wife, right?
你已经有老婆了吧？

433
00:30:56,640 --> 00:30:59,160
- Kambura. - That's right.
-坎布拉  -是的

434
00:31:00,560 --> 00:31:02,440
Why did you call me here, Cemil?
你为什么给我打电话，塞米尔？

435
00:31:03,360 --> 00:31:04,760
What do you want from me?
你想从我这里得到什么？

436
00:31:05,440 --> 00:31:07,240
What are you doing with that gun?
你用那把枪做什么？

437
00:31:08,000 --> 00:31:09,400
Blowing out tyres.
打轮胎

438
00:31:11,000 --> 00:31:12,240
I heard.
我听说了

439
00:31:12,320 --> 00:31:14,400
I heard it all the way in Istanbul.
我在伊斯坦布尔就听说了

440
00:31:15,920 --> 00:31:17,320
I'm sure it did.
当然了

441
00:31:19,000 --> 00:31:21,120
Selim will be alright, Nesrin.
内斯林，塞利姆会没事的

442
00:31:21,720 --> 00:31:23,320
No one's going to hurt him.
没有人会伤害他

443
00:31:24,280 --> 00:31:26,040
All we ask...
我只是想问……

444
00:31:26,640 --> 00:31:31,480
- Is that his imaginary remorse... - Imaginary?
-那是他想象中的悔恨……—想象中的?

445
00:31:31,560 --> 00:31:32,480
Exactly.
正是

446
00:31:32,560 --> 00:31:35,400
He should keep it to himself.
他应该保密的

447
00:31:36,040 --> 00:31:37,040
Quietly.
悄悄的

448
00:31:38,440 --> 00:31:41,280
Let's say you successfully shut Selim up.
假设你成功让塞利姆闭嘴了

449
00:31:43,120 --> 00:31:45,800
What will you do with Ufuk?
你会对乌福克做什么？

450
00:31:48,360 --> 00:31:51,000
How will you shut that poor boy up?
你怎么让那个可怜的男孩闭嘴？

451
00:31:52,600 --> 00:31:53,960
Why would I shut him up?
我为什么要把他闭嘴？

452
00:31:55,080 --> 00:31:56,960
He's talking as we speak.
在我们聊天的同时他正在说

453
00:31:57,960 --> 00:32:00,040
Talking to whom, you may ask.
你可能会问他在跟谁说

454
00:32:01,560 --> 00:32:04,040
He's talking to that beautiful daughter of yours.
他在跟你那个美丽的女儿说话

455
00:32:05,040 --> 00:32:09,120
Nevra doesn't realize that Ufuk is a troubled man.
内芙拉没有意识到乌福克是个很麻烦的人

456
00:32:09,960 --> 00:32:15,000
For years now, he's confessed to arson to every cop he ran across.
多年来，他对他遇到的每个警察都承认纵火

457
00:32:15,920 --> 00:32:18,400
You should let Nevra know the next time you see her.
下次见到内芙拉时，你应该告诉她

458
00:32:19,200 --> 00:32:22,080
He is a certified loon. He doesn't know what he's saying.
他是一个疯子  他根本不知道自己在说什么。

459
00:32:25,880 --> 00:32:28,440
Don't you ever wonder what really happened?
你难道不想知道到底发生了什么吗？

460
00:32:28,520 --> 00:32:31,440
- About? - The truth.
-关于什么？  -真相

461
00:32:33,480 --> 00:32:34,480
No.
不想

462
00:32:35,720 --> 00:32:37,880
So you don't want to know.
所以你根本不想知道

463
00:32:40,880 --> 00:32:42,960
I'm loyal to my wife, Nesrin.
我忠于我的妻子  内斯林

464
00:32:44,200 --> 00:32:46,600
You know what true loyalty is?
你知道什么是真正的忠诚吗？

465
00:32:48,440 --> 00:32:50,160
Never questioning.
永不质疑

466
00:32:53,240 --> 00:32:55,520
In other words, deceiving yourself.
换句话说，欺骗自己

467
00:32:58,480 --> 00:32:59,680
Have you ever...
你有没有……

468
00:33:00,640 --> 00:33:04,000
loved anyone so much that you'd never question anything?
像这样爱过什么人，你永远都不会质疑任何事情？

469
00:33:04,680 --> 00:33:05,920
Have you ever...
你有没有……

470
00:33:06,520 --> 00:33:09,520
believed in something no matter what?
不论发生什么都会一直坚信某件事？

471
00:33:10,080 --> 00:33:12,320
Of course not. Never.
当然没有，从没有过

472
00:33:18,400 --> 00:33:19,600
I guess...
我猜……

473
00:33:21,120 --> 00:33:23,400
you must've never had a family, Nesrin.
你一定从未拥有过家庭，内斯林

474
00:33:28,680 --> 00:33:32,960
KAMBURA POLICE DEPARTMENT
坎布拉警察署

475
00:33:33,040 --> 00:33:34,760
You didn't cuff me.
你没给我戴手铐

476
00:33:35,560 --> 00:33:39,120
- You promised you'd arrest me. - Don't you realize the state he's in?
-你答应过要逮捕我  -你不知道他什么状态吗？

477
00:33:39,200 --> 00:33:41,800
Let us talk to him and we will.
让我们跟他谈

478
00:33:42,360 --> 00:33:44,040
Thank you for all your help.
谢谢你的帮助

479
00:33:45,120 --> 00:33:47,440
Tell it from the beginning.
从最开始说起

480
00:33:47,960 --> 00:33:50,280
- I already did. - Tell it again.
-我已经说过了  -再说一次

481
00:33:50,360 --> 00:33:52,400
How many times do I need to tell it?
我需要说多少次？

482
00:33:52,480 --> 00:33:55,320
I thought you were proper cops. I burnt the house down!
我以为你们是真正的警察  是我把房子烧毁了！

483
00:33:55,400 --> 00:33:59,120
I killed all those people! What else is there to say?
我杀了他们！还有什么要说的？

484
00:34:00,840 --> 00:34:03,440
It seems you won't do your job, either.
看来你也不会抓我的

485
00:34:04,280 --> 00:34:06,560
I'm not telling you anything.
我什么都没告诉你

486
00:34:07,160 --> 00:34:10,120
I'll keep telling it to myself.
我将会继续告诉自己

487
00:34:11,800 --> 00:34:14,080
I'm so sick of this. I'm so sick of it.
我很讨厌这样  我很讨厌

488
00:34:14,160 --> 00:34:16,480
I can do it myself. I don't need you.
我自己可以做  不需要你

489
00:34:17,120 --> 00:34:19,520
Where do you think you're going?
你以为你要去哪里？

490
00:34:19,600 --> 00:34:21,320
Where do you think you're going!
你以为你要去哪里？

491
00:34:21,400 --> 00:34:25,240
You're just standing there. You haven't even put me in cuffs!
你只是站在那儿  你甚至都没有把我戴上手铐！

492
00:34:25,320 --> 00:34:27,360
Fuck you and your cuffs!
去尼玛的手铐！

493
00:34:29,640 --> 00:34:33,200
You there! Look here! Come here! Quick!
你！这边！过来！快！

494
00:34:33,280 --> 00:34:34,800
Give me that!
手铐给我！

495
00:34:37,080 --> 00:34:39,240
Hold out your hands! Hold them out!
伸出双手，伸出双手！

496
00:34:42,360 --> 00:34:45,600
There you go! There's your cuffs!
好了！现在你有手铐了！

497
00:34:47,560 --> 00:34:49,000
Let me talk to him alone.
让我跟他单独谈谈

498
00:34:50,560 --> 00:34:51,560
Are you sure?
你确定吗？

499
00:34:52,760 --> 00:34:56,000
I'll be right outside. Yell if you need anything.
如果你需要什么，我就在门口

500
00:35:13,080 --> 00:35:17,280
You were the one I was chasing that night, right?
你就是那天晚上我追的那个人，对吗？

501
00:35:18,840 --> 00:35:20,880
Why did you want me to see it, Ufuk?
乌福克，你为什么要我看到它？

502
00:35:22,600 --> 00:35:25,520
Why did you want the truth to come out after all these years?
过了这么多年，你为什么要现在说出真相？

503
00:35:26,840 --> 00:35:28,360
After all these years?
过了这么多年？

504
00:35:29,000 --> 00:35:31,560
I've been imploring the cops ever since the incident.
自事件发生以来我一直在恳求警察

505
00:35:31,640 --> 00:35:34,640
Telling them that I did it. That they should arrest me.
告诉他们是我做的  他们应该逮捕我

506
00:35:36,200 --> 00:35:38,840
I've been shouting it from the rooftops for ten years.
我已经说了十年

507
00:35:40,560 --> 00:35:42,480
But no one will listen.
但是没人听

508
00:35:44,120 --> 00:35:45,440
Then they leave.
然后他们离开这里

509
00:35:46,040 --> 00:35:47,760
Others take their place.
其他人接替他们的位置

510
00:35:48,400 --> 00:35:51,640
I tell them. They don't listen, either.
我告诉他们  他们也不听

511
00:35:53,160 --> 00:35:55,280
I heard Nesrin's daughter had become a cop.
听说内斯林的女儿当了警察

512
00:35:55,880 --> 00:35:56,960
I thought that maybe...
我以为

513
00:35:57,800 --> 00:35:59,680
Maybe she'd listen to me.
也许她会听我的

514
00:36:01,520 --> 00:36:03,160
But how was I supposed to find you?
但是我应该怎么找到你呢？

515
00:36:05,160 --> 00:36:08,280
Then, one day, you appeared in Kambura.
然后，有一天你突然出现在坎布拉

516
00:36:13,400 --> 00:36:15,120
Do you have any trash, Naz?
纳兹，你有垃圾吗？

517
00:36:15,920 --> 00:36:17,440
Your door's unlocked.
你的门没锁

518
00:36:18,120 --> 00:36:19,400
Naz?
纳兹？

519
00:36:20,640 --> 00:36:22,680
Are you home? It's Seyit.
你在家里吗？我是塞菲

520
00:36:37,480 --> 00:36:41,200
Who else was there with you on the night of the fire?
火灾当晚还有谁跟你在一起？

521
00:36:42,320 --> 00:36:43,600
I don't remember.
我不记得了

522
00:36:44,400 --> 00:36:46,280
But everyone was there. I'm sure of it.
